Privacy & Terms
2023/12/12
Last updated on November 22, 2021
Mini World: CREATA is a sandbox game, where users are encouraged to play and create whatever they can imagine. Your privacy is important to us; this is why we created this Privacy Policy so that you are aware of what information is collected, how we use it, and who we share it with.
This summary is to help you navigate the Privacy Policy and it is not a substitute for reading everything, so please read this Privacy Policy carefully! You can jump to the particular sections if you would like to learn more about how we process your information.
What information do we collect?
If you register an account to use Mini World: CREATA then we will need some information such as your contact details, device information, region and age to set this up. If you choose, you can provide certain other information or participate in surveys about Mini World: CREATA. We will also process your information to allow you to send or post messages, process your payments, conduct analytics and address any concerns you may have.
How will we use your information?
We use your information to provide Mini World: CREATA, to keep your account secure, understand your use of Mini World: CREATA, and to support and improve Mini World: CREATA. We do not share your information with any third parties, except where we need to in order to provide Mini World: CREATA or where we are instructed to by a court, authority or compelled by law to provide your information.
Who do we share your information with?
We use some third parties to help us deliver Mini World: CREATA and to process or store your information for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. We may be required by a court or legal obligation to disclose certain information in some circumstances.
Where do we process your information?
We process your information in the People’s Republic of China and the United States.
How long do we keep your information?
We generally retain your information for the period during which you maintain an account for Mini World: CREATA, after which time your data is deleted (as further described in this Privacy Policy), unless otherwise required by applicable laws.
How can I exercise my rights over my information?
Depending on where you are, you may have certain rights with respect to your information, such as rights of access or data deletion.
Contact us
You can contact us at miniwantech@gmail.com if you have any questions or want to exercise any rights you may have.
1.              About Mini World: CREATA and this Privacy Policy
Mini World: CREATA is a sandbox game, where users are encouraged to play and create whatever they can imagine. As a user of Mini World: CREATA, you and your friends can play games, collaborate on building or just gather and explore other users’ creations. Your privacy is important to us; this is why we created this Privacy Policy so that you are aware of what information is collected, how we use it, and who we share it with.
This Privacy Policy covers our website https://www.miniworldgame.com/ (“Website”) and our Mini World: CREATA game (“Service”), on which an authorized link to this Privacy Policy is posted. This Privacy Policy covers our practices with regard to users of all ages, including those users under the age of 18 (“children”). The Service is operated by or on behalf of Miniwan Technology Co., Limited, a company with its registered address at 19H Maxgrand Plaza, No 3 Tai Yau Street, San Po Kong, Kowloon, Hong Kong (“Miniwan”).
If you are an EEA or United Kingdom resident, this whole Privacy Policy applies to you. If you are a resident of California, please refer to the California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”) Appendix.
Miniwan is committed to protecting the privacy of our users, including children. Please see the “Children’s Privacy” and “Protection of Children’s Data and Parental Controls” sections below for more information about your rights as a parent or legal guardian of our children users and the measures we take to afford children users with additional protections and comply with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”).
It is important for you to understand how the collection and use of your Personal Data happens and how you may control your Personal Data. When you use the Service, you accept our rules and policies regarding your Personal Data and you agree to us collecting, processing, using and storing your Personal Data, as described in this Privacy Policy.
You acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with anything set out in this Privacy Policy, you must not use the Service and play the Mini World: CREATA game. If you continue to use the Service and play the Mini World: CREATA game, you are deemed to have agreed with the Privacy Policy.
You are under no obligation to provide Personal Data to us when requested. However, if you choose to withhold any requested information, we may not be able to provide you with the Service or allow you to play the Mini World: CREATA game or use certain of its features.
If you have any questions, comments, or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy and/or our data practices, please contact us at the following e-mail address, or mailing address:
Contact: miniwantech@gmail.com
Data Controller: Miniwan Technology Co., Limited
Address: 19H Maxgrand Plaza, No 3 Tai Yau Street, San Po Kong, Kowloon, Hong Kong
2.              Definitions
“Personal Data” means any information relating to a natural person who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data, or an online identifier.
“Processing” means any operation which is performed on Personal Data, such as collection, recording, organization, structuring, storage, adaptation or any kind of disclosure or other use.
Any other capitalized term that is not defined in this Privacy Policy is defined (and has the meaning) set out in our Terms of Use.
3.              Information Collected on our Website
Please note that our Websites (en.mini1.cn and their subdomains) are general audience websites. On these sites, we may provide information regarding the Service updates, press information, and other general audience information. We may also ask for your name, email address, if you send us a message or other information so that we can provide information in relation to your request. No game play happens on the Websites. As such, the parts of this Privacy Policy that discuss game play or discuss children users under 13 are not applicable to the Website.
4.              Children’s Privacy
Mini World: CREATA is not intended to be used by anyone under the age of 18 years (or as otherwise specified in the table below where the minimum age differs) (“Minimum Age”) without the consent of their parent or legal guardian. We will ask users to provide their age-related information before they use Mini World: CREATA Works for the first time. If the date of birth entered by a user indicates that they are below the Minimum Age, we may take steps to confirm that the user has obtained their parent’s or legal guardian’s consent prior to letting them use Mini World: CREATA.
If you are under the Minimum Age, you are required to obtain parental or legal guardian consent prior to using or playing the Service. If you do not get such permission, you should not use our Service.
