5.              Protection of Children’s Data and Parental Controls
We recognize that children deserve added protections with regard to their Personal Data and privacy online. For this reason, when users under the Minimum Age register for the Service with the parent’s or legal guardian’s consent, will not have access to certain features.
To make any requests for changes to your child’s account or requests for the removal of Personal Data collected about you or your child from our Service (as applicable), or to request that we stop the further collection or use of your or your child’s Personal Data in connection with the Service (as applicable), please contact us at miniwantech@gmail.com.
We proactively filter all public and comment areas of the Service (such as chat, forums, group walls, personal posts, etc.) to remove references to addresses, emails, phone numbers, or other Personal Data regardless of security and privacy settings. All text is also filtered for profanity, phishing, and adult or suggestive content. Our system uses a combination of human and automated processes. However, like all filtering technology, our systems are not 100% effective. We strongly encourage children who use any interactive features on our Service never to provide Personal Data about themselves or a third party, and certainly never to attempt to circumvent our filters or moderation. We also recommend that parents and legal guardians carefully supervise their children when the children participate in online activities.
In general, we will not use or share account information (including Personal Data) from your child’s account, except for the permissible purposes stated in this Privacy Policy, and, if required by law, only with the prior verifiable consent of a parent or legal guardian.
6.              How Mini World: CREATA Works
This is how Mini World: CREATA works:
When you sign up to Mini World: CREATA as a new user, a user ID (UID) is created automatically for you. A virtual character is generated to represent your identity in the Mini World: CREATA. Users should not create a user name that reflects their own name or other Personal Data. Users should also not pick a password that is easy to guess, and should not share their password.
Users interact with other users through in-game, personal text and voice messaging. Users can remove friends or delete their accounts to restrict or disable communications with other users.
Each user is given one or more pieces of virtual real space on which they can unlock items and characters, ripe golden fruit, trade in the game and accelerate the growth of their gardens.
Users search for, find, and play games made by other users. They play these games with other users around the world, and are identified only by their user ID.
The Mini World: CREATA includes virtual currency known as Mini Coins and Mini Beans, 1 Mini Coins=60 Mini Beans; users can purchase Mini coins and Mini Beans in a variety of ways, and use them to buy items for their characters, for in-game items, and other uses.
For more information on how our Service works, please see our Terms of Service.
